# Vercel needs:
#   - pnorm/data/explorer.html     (the lean HTML + JS shell; ~1.4 MB)
#   - pnorm/data/layers/*.png      (per-layer rasters, ~50 KB each, lazy-loaded)
#   - vercel.json
# Everything else in pnorm/data/ is multi-GB local research state (OSM
# extracts, OSRM tile dirs, per-city heatmap HTML, sidecar K×K matrices)
# that's gitignored but would otherwise be uploaded by `vercel deploy`.
#
# The lazy-load architecture (scripts/build_explorer.py) writes per-layer
# PNGs to data/layers/<key>__<field>.png; the HTML inlines only NYC's
# default layer for instant first paint and fetches the rest on demand.
pnorm/data/*
!pnorm/data/explorer.html
!pnorm/data/layers/

# Local-only directories
.venv/
.vercel/
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
.ruff_cache/
.pytest_cache/
.ipynb_checkpoints/
pnorm/notebooks/

# Backup branch artifacts
backup-pre-rewrite*
